cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about end-to-end Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) using attention-based methods and Connectionist Temporal Classification (CTC) network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests the sub-categories cs.SD (Sound) and cs.LG (Learning) as likely options. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible options.
